I love this place. Their wings are some of the best in town and are getting me through the pandemic. Also highly recommend the barbacoa bowl. Great people too. Jenn Richter’s comments are horrible and not true. I also had a salad. IT WAS THE FRESHEST. AND I LOVED THE AMBIANCE. WONDERFUL PEOPLE. WONDERFUL CLIENTELE. I think she may have rated the wrong place... maybe that review was meant for the 7/11 she works at.

Came here on Labor Day weekend for a salad and a drink, and unfortunately the southwest salad with crispy chicken was very poorly made - I assume due to the pandemic causing fresh produce to go bad quicker? Though I would hope there would be quality checks. It felt thrown together with whatever was left available. The tomatoes were bad, avocado was too ripe, there was not enough lettuce, dressing mixed in without asking, overall pretty sparse. Crispy chicken tasted reheated or frozen/over-cooked. I really wanted to say something but felt really bad bc I saw that they now add a COVID operational surcharge. Though because of that, it deserves pointing out.  I will say the employees are great, very friendly people which is why I give them 3 stars. I was however very disappointed to see about 12 cops hang out here during their afternoon shift, and that was something that really rubbed me the wrong way during the civil unrest as the optics were a bit threatening. Just felt that also warranted pointing out.
One of my favorite locations for quality Bar food. Got there near seven, it wasn't very crowded. It has a great interior. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I loved.
Great scene for delicious bar food. Visited at eight, it was not full. The service was very kind and attentive. Prices are fair.

A great tavern with a laid back, neighborhood feel. Friendly staff that were knowledgeable about their beers and personable. The food was very good and fresh with simple but appealing plating. Definitely a must try.

Very cool atmosphere, exceptional drink specials, food was on point, and the staff was friendly and attentive. I got to chatting with the GM and he was pretty cool, too. I’ll definitely back and would absolutely recommend stopping in to others.

Small spot tucked away. Plenty of places to sit, cold drinks and good food. You can come for the trivia, a sporting event or just to eat either way you'll enjoy your time

The Caesar salad bowl is made from crispy parmesan cheese. So. Awesome. And the old fashioned here is great. Went on a Thursday, it was not crowded at all, and Serena Williams was crushing it on the TV.
Great food, good beer selection, great specials, and friendly staff.

When I come to town, we always have a great time here!

Staff is so genuine and friendly. I ordered a SW Chicken Salad to go and they were very accommodating with my request to please chop the salad (needed to eat one handed). The salad was delicious and fresh! Unfortunately, the chicken was WAY over done and dry. However, I thought the salad was so good that I ate it anyway. I chalk it up to a one-time thing and will be going back.
Friendly service. Great drinks.
Great food love their burgers and fair prices for the area
I've been coming here for years. I love this place. Awesome employee's, outstanding food, and very good drinks.
4 dollar cans and bottles on Monday and half priced apps!

Avoid this place for food!  They are clearly not using proper kitchen sanitation techniques.  I ate about 2 full tacos and thought the beer was messing with my appetite ... a few hours later I didn't feel well and (again) blamed it on the beers.        Around midnight or so I felt extremely restless, chills, then hot, upset stomach.    I eventually became violently ill and vomited.  Disclaimer: the following may be gross to some people.    While vomiting I pulled a small piece of raw, marinated steak from the bowl.   I'm not a doctor but I know I shouldn't still have undigested food in my stomach 12 hours later.    I know it was raw marinated steak because I smashed it in my fingers and smelled it.  Anyway -   Here we are a week later, I'm down 10lbs .. have zero appetite, extremely anxious feeling,   Chills,  still feel like whatever is inside is still working It's way out.
Awesome local bar with superb food and a great beer selection! Fun happy hour and always friendly staff!
Best Bacon Burger and Coleslaw I've had in Chicago.  The coleslaw is made with vinegar instead of mayo or whatever milk-based ingredient makes it white.  DELICIOUS!

The food here is excellent.  Had the burger with parm truffle fries, the steak tacos, the shrimp tacos and all were way better than I expected.   Good beer list too.  The service can be a little slow when it gets busy, but it's good enough to make me want to go back.
Fish tacos and wings are good!
Quality food with nice atmosphere

Been here a couple times now. Bar food is great for what it is. Lunchtime during the work week can get pretty packed, I'd recommend a reservation. Not a bad place to watch a game on the weekends either. Staff is friendly too.

The staff is very friendly - has the feel of a hometown pub.  Nice selection of beer on draft. Good comfort food.  On Mondays they have half-price  appetizers and all of the bottles of beer are only $4.00.
An affordable place near the loop with a good beer menu!

This place has a good selection of craft/bottled beers and the food specials are pretty damn good. Be sure to have the boneless wings tossed in the soyracha sauce. It's soy saice, Sriracha and honey. My all time favorite wing sauce. The manager, Patrick is a prince .He is super friendly and great with the customers. Makes you feel like you're at home!

A little pricey but great food, beer, sports and service. I am a gigantic nerd so didn't care for the sports. However the waiter and I talked video games and kept the beer flowing like the salmon of Capistrano. A bbq sandwich later I was about to fall out of my chair asleep. (in a good way). This place is cozy and cool.

Great food, especially the apps! Half price on Mondays as well. Lots of Tv's and great service.

Great location off the Clinton Green line stop and right next to French market. Nice staff/service. Very warm on a very cold December day. I would say it takes it a notch up from regular bar food, however, its more expensive than I would go to for bar food, and when Im drunk I dont really care that the food is marginally better than the average bar. I went on a quiet night, so looked like there was a lot of space, but I can imagine it gets crowded.
Food is reasonably priced and well prepared.  Space is not large so seating can be tight.  Is so loud during lunch hours and after work hours.

Bar food, but good bar food. Garlic fries are great, and beer selection is good enough. Get there early for lunch though, not enough seats to handle the demand.

It's kiddy corner from where I work, so I've been here multiple times. It always seems to be overcrowded, and seating for groups 4+ is almost impossible, there might be one area to accommodate this. Also, the service is generally slow and I've gotten unwaranted attitude from the server more than once. The food is their only redeeming quality, but not worth all the other BS, IMO. I would strongly recommend going a couple blocks to Jefferson Tap instead.

Nice beer selection, average bar food, slim, long floor plan, makes it difficult to get around the bar. Usually crowded though, I guess the beer selection must be the reason. The service was good, was comped appetizers once because of a mix up. It's okay but nothing major.

Great Happy hour Specials - Delicious Tacos and margaritas!  I've been here many times with friends after work, the atmosphere is relaxed, and it's not usually packed earlier in the in the week.  The drinks are reasonably priced and they have a decent craft beer selection. I would also recommend their Tacos - any and all of them, so so so good. Of course, the rest of their food is good too, but definitely and unexpected place to get a decent taco.
Really decent draft selection, and very convenient location-right next to the train station. $4 drafts on Monday.

Underrated but to people that know this area this place have a good bar menu and line up of draft beer.  Great value for a near downtown bar and restaurant.  Particularly good is the Santa Fe egg rolls.

This may well become my new Sunday haunt. Why? Sunday = half-price apps (BF and I split the sliders with sweet potato fries, quesedilla and jalepeno wontons; I'd get the latter two again) and free bar trivia at 7:00. Also, reasonable prices on a great beer selection. Friendly staff. Cool vibe.
Watered down drinks
great food. i miss the mac and cheese bites. overall solid bar food.

Good environment and the service is great. Food is a typical bar food with a few variations but they have a great trivia night on Sundays and some random specials throughout the week that are more than worth it.

Service is great.  It's a wonderful environment and trivia on Sunday nights make it an even better hang-out spot.  They have plenty of TV's for all sports events. The food is okay.  Typical bar food. I would recommend this place to anyone looking to hang out with friends and not spend copious amounts on drinks and appetizers.
Prices are good. Go here Sunday night for trivia

New Line Tavern is a neighborhoody spot in the West Loop where you'll find many business professionals enjoying happy hour after work. The food is good and reasonably priced (I recommend the black bean burger) and comes in well-sized portions. Can get a little crowded at night but you'll be in good company. The bartenders are friendly and knowledgeable and will help you pick a beer that meets your personal preferences.

If you are in the neighborhood or close by it's a pretty nice local bar to stop by and grab a beer.  Their selection of draft beer is pretty good and the bartender was really pleasant to have a short conversation with.  There are plenty of bars in area and this one has it's own unique experience.
The preztel burger is good.  The atmosphere is a bit loud, it can be difficult to have a conversation.

Went here before beerfest (at union station) to grab a bite to eat. Good 'gastro pub' food. The service wasn't the best as there was only 1 waitress there for the whole bar/restaurant. Bathrooms were modern & clean. Yay!
Excellent organic Turkey burgers! The fries are delicious and the service is excellent. They always have the best Chicago sports events on their many TV's and the music is great too.
Great lunch burger place. Decent beer selection. Hot waitresses. I like it.
